title: Aleksandar Alempijević
text:
Aleksandar Alempijević (, born July 25, 1988) is a <a href="Serbs">Serbian</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> player who plays as a <a href="Midfielder%20%28association%20football%29%23Defensive-midfielder">defensive midfielder</a>.
Career.
Born in <a href="%C4%8Ca%C4%8Dak">Čačak</a>, <a href="SR%20Serbia">SR Serbia</a>, <a href="SFR%20Yugoslavia">SFR Yugoslavia</a>, he started playing with <a href="FK%20Partizan">FK Partizan</a> youth team. Between 2006 and 2008 he played 2 seasons with Partizan satellite club <a href="FK%20Teleoptik">FK Teleoptik</a> in Serbian third tier. In 2008, he moved to Hungary and joined <a href="Kecskem%C3%A9ti%20TE">Kecskeméti TE</a> where he played the following 4 seasons. In summer 2012 he moved to <a href="Ferencv%C3%A1rosi%20TC">Ferencvárosi TC</a>. In September 2013, after playing 5 seasons in the <a href="Nemzeti%20Bajnoks%C3%A1g%20I">Nemzeti Bajnokság I</a>, he returned to Serbia and joined top league side <a href="FK%20Javor%20Ivanjica">FK Javor Ivanjica</a>.
